Product name: Horse Nursery Decor - Wooden Rocking Horse - Vintage Rocking Horse - Horse Decor - Vintage First Birthday - Riding Horse - Wooden Horse Toy
Description:
Due to the lack of space, we are parting with our family pet Charlie. This lovely vintage wooden horse has been in our family since I was my kids age (lets just say about 24 years ago). My kids have loved it throughout the years and now its time for others to love him as well. We believe Charlie is about 45 years young and still kicking; he has his original wool hair (good vintage condition) and beautiful little tan leather ears. The wood is in great condition for being loved as much as it was. He has so much personality and has brought our family so much joy. He is regularly exercised and loves to be feed at least four carrots a day. We are willing to part with Charlie to the right family. Please be aware he is a handful and loves attention. If you notice by his photographs, Charlie lost his reign many many moons ago but that hasn't stopped him from being a showstopper. Here are his most recent measurements (since he is a mature horse, he should not grow any more then what is listed): 
Runners are 32” long, Charlie is about 11" wide at the base and measures about 30" tall (measuring the tallest point). He weighs about 15 lbs (he's been watching his figure)

Description:
This cool shirt is perfect for any camping themed party and is sure to be a hit!

Applique is done on my home embroidery machine and care instructions will be included. Back of embroidery is covered with a special material that protects little one's skin. 
***************************************************************
Shirts are 100% cotton knit jersey, youth are 50/50 blend when available.
***PLEASE PAY CLOSE ATTENTION TO THE MEASUREMENTS IN THE SIZE CHARTS PROVIDED. In my opinion, the toddler 4 and 5/6 run wide. For this reason, I highly recommend going to a youth XS (4-5). Also, the youth shirt sizes are marked a little differently than some other brands as, for some reason, they switched the way they marked the shirt sizes this year. For example, a medium used to be an 8 and a large was a 10/12 but this supplier recently changed their size tags to a medium being a 10/12. However, other brands that run similar in length and width for each size are still tagged M(8) and L (10/12). If your child typically wears a M from a department store, the M in this brand will still fit, it will just be marked M 10/12 instead of the typical M (8) seen on brands in most stores. My son, for example wears a 10/12 pretty much everywhere and a large in plain T's. I still order him the large in this shirt as it fits the same as the other larges, it is just marked L (14/16) instead of L (10/12) as seen on Fruit of the Loom or Hanes T's. It is your responsibility to check the size charts provided and ensure you are ordering the correct size for your child. If you have any questions, I am happy to answer them. 
As you will note on the spec sheets, 24m and 2T have the same measurements. I may substitute one for the other depending on which I have in stock at the time. All measurements are shown, just zoom in on the photo. Measurements shown are garment measurements. Measure the length and width of a shirt that fits your child and compare those to the measurements in the chart to determine what size to order.

Product name: Antique Victorian Crescent Moon Locket Necklace, Gold Filled Locket, Crescent Moon Flower Spray Locket, Celestial Locket, Pink Springtime
Description:
Lovely! Springtime collection! 
This antique gold filled locket dates to the Victorian era  (c. - late 1800s to early 1900s). Featuring a lovely crescent moon design with a flower spray on the left side. The moon is made up of (7) clear paste stones. A few have darkened with age.  Etching is nice and sharp, there are (2) pink stones for the center of each flower. Inside it opens to reveal two areas in which to place your keepsake photos. Both frames and plastic covers are intact. It hangs from a new, long gold filled satellite chain -spring clasp closure. Total weight of locket and chain is 14.2 grams.
*Age:
Late 1800s - Early 1900s
*Measurements:
Locket is a little over 1-1/8" in diameter.
Chain is 22" in length.
Total weight of locket and chain is 14.2 grams.
*Condition:
In great antique condition. Fully functional - opens and snaps shut securely. Both frames and plastic covers are intact. Minor scratching on front of locket about middle of crescent (pictured). Does not affect the beauty of the piece. Some stones have darkened with age.
*History:
The crescent moon motif locket became popular during the later Victorian period which ran from about 1880 - 1901. The reasoning behind the emergence of this celestial theme was in part due to the great number of astronomical events, such as the appearance of Halley’s Comet during this time frame. In addition, travel to such exotic places as the Middle East and the lands of the Ottoman Empire gave rise to the exposure of the crescent moon as an integrated symbol for the area.
I am in LOVE with these lockets and think they’re absolutely stunning, and I really love the meaning behind each one. I often feel like I am wearing a piece of history when I wear a vintage locket. I wonder who originally wore the locket, what they looked like and what it meant to them. 
When shopping for the holidays or any special occasion, I love finding gifts that are not only unique and thoughtful, but the perfect gift that matches the special person I’m gifting to. I also love having personalized items of my own and there’s nothing better than wearing or using something that is unique to you and expresses who you are or how you feel.
Antique and vintage items are shipped with insurance and tracking.

Product name: Moroccan Kilim Rug - Colorful Boucherouite Rag Carpet - Eco-Friendly Home Design
Description:
Handmade from recycled fabrics, this rug is the showstopping centerpiece for any room. It features graphic Berber patterns woven from vibrant red, yellow, light blue, and gray fabric on a cream/light pink background. The upper pile is made from fabric and the base is reinforced with wool. It measures 4'2" by 7'5.5" (1.27 m x 2.27 m) and weights 18.6 pounds (8.44 kg).
Boucherouite carpets are a play on the traditional rag rug, but with a vibrant Moroccan twist. These rugs are known for their wild colors and crazy, sometimes psychedelic designs. You'll never find two rugs exactly the same - each is as unique as the woman who made it. Women traditionally constructed boucherouite rugs out of fabric scraps, used clothes, spare wool, and any other materials they could get their hands on. Boucherouite rugs are eco-friendly, made from almost 100% recycled materials. They are colorful, fun, and the perfect complement to both modern and rustic decor.
All of our products were handmade by Berber women, and each carpet is an original work of art. There may be imperfections in the pattern, or the carpets might be slightly longer in one direction. Each carpet has its own character, as you can see in the photos above. Thank you for shopping with Two Camel Carpets!

Bakelite semichrome tested positive
Bakelite is a phenolic resin - a distillate of coal tar and formaldehyde. Leo Baekeland discovered it when he was looking for a substitute for shellac - using money he made selling the patent for photographic paper to Eastman Kodak!  A thermoset plastic (didn't change when heated). Carved pieces were usually done so by hand.

Product name: Blonde mink fur stole, tourmaline, thick, luxurious, soft, light and dark shading, Solmar Furs, original brochure, tag, 1950s
Description:
VINTAGE TOURMALINE MINK FUR STOLE (Ref: 160602)
DESCRIPTION
This is a gorgeous and luxurious tourmaline or blonde mink fur stole.
The fur is thick and soft. 
It has interesting variations of light and dark shades. The fur closest to the pelt is a light blonde color.
The stole is long, wide, and shaped so that it fits around the neck and shoulders nicely.
It has a clever stitched down collar and long fur pelt tassels at each end.
It is fully lined in light taupe colored satin and has a satin loop on one side so that one end of the stole can be slipped under the loop and be held in place. It also has a single fur clip for the same purpose.
The label on the inside says "Genuine Natural Mink".
The stole came in its original department store box (David Jones) with its original tag, original brochure with all sorts of information about buying and caring for fur, original red ribbon, and original tissue paper. The original tag identifies the item as a "Tourmaline Mink Stole".
The brand is "Solmar", a now defunct Australian company.
It is a beautifully made, high quality item.
It would make a great wrap for a winter wedding or a night out.
MEASUREMENTS
The measurements are taken on the inside along the lining, not the fur.
With the stole folded in half, the inside length (the length that touches the neck) measures 27 inches / 69 cm and the outside length measures 29.5 inches / 75.5 cm.
The stole measures 16 inches / 41 cm wide in the middle and 5.5 inches / 14 cm wide at each end.
The tassels measure 6 inches / 15 cm long.
It is a one size fits most people item.
AGE
The stole is 1950s. 
CONDITION
The stole is in excellent vintage condition and has been stored well. The fur is in beautiful condition and the stole has no tears or rips. It has one mark on the lining that is 1 inch / 2.5 cm square. It is a darker shade of taupe than the rest of the lining. See last photo.
POSTAGE
If you purchase more than one item I combine postage, if possible, and refund any postage overages.
The item will be shipped without its original box because the box adds weight, size, and cost to the shipping and it is just a basic cardboard box. Shipping will be provided by Australia Post.
Thank you for visiting CardCurios. If you have any questions, please convo me.

Product name: Vintage Hair Comb Butterfly Design Faux Tortoiseshell Small Peineta Decorative Hair Comb Art Nouveau B105
Description:
Vintage 1950s butterfly peineta, small hair comb,  with butterfly design on faux tortoiseshell plastic.
Mid Century decorative small peineta, or small comb, is made of plastic to imitate the tortoise shell combs of the Victorian age.
Victorian ladies did not cut their hair but needed combs to keep it off their necks and out of their faces. They never wore their hair long out in public.
Modern ladies used small decorative hair combs to hold up their mantillas, or head coverings. 
They are still used today for religious worship and quinceaneras.
This comb is not Victorian and has an Art Nouveau pattern of butterflies.
Made of molded plastic, it is a faux tortoise shell look.
See photos for measurements.

Description:
The Bouvier des Flandres served farmers and cattle merchants in southwest Flanders and on the French northern plain. Bouvier means oxherd in French, although the dogs were more often called Vuilbaard (dirty beard) or Koe Hand (cow dog). Besides its main duty as a cattle drover, the Bouvier was an all-round farm dog, functioning also as a livestock and farm guard and draft dog.
Whether you are looking for a Bouvier des Flandres artwork, a Bouvier des Flandres print or a Bouvier des Flandres gift for yourself or a Bouvier des Flandres lover, you will find that this artwork fits perfectly in any home.
Description of Bouvier des Flandres Artwork - - - - - - -
First, I researched the Bouvier des Flandres breed and then I created each illustration that  reflects the breed's special traits. An owner can display what makes the Bouvier des Flandres unique. 
Designed with love and then carefully matted, this piece comes ready to frame with a gorgeous 1.5” black textured frame making it measure in at 11” x 14” - so it's just the right fit for a standard 11” x 14” frame.
Carefully hand signed and dated, this illustration will be shipped by USPS First Class postage on the day of your order. It takes 3-4 days to land on your doorstop, depending on how fast (or slow!) the postal system is going that week.

Description:
Trade out your pet's disposable bedding for a snuggly, and reusable option! Fleece cage liners are 100% machine washable and reusable! Gone are the days of spending money on countless bags of paper bedding and wood shavings!
These fleece cage liners are made with 100% polyester fleece and have UHAUL padding sandwiched in between for absorbency. The top layer of fleece features your choice of patterned material, while the bottom layer boasts a coordinating solid. ***If you have a coordinating color preference, please note your choice of solid in the "Notes to Seller" section before checkout. If left unspecified, a coordinating color will be chosen for you.***
Have another design or color scheme in mind? Send me a convo and have a CUSTOM ORDER made JUST FOR YOU. 
Need a custom size that's not listed? Specify your dimensions in "notes to seller" and have a liner made to YOUR EXACT CAGE SIZE.
Liners fit cages with the following dimensions:
1x2 C&C - 14"x28"
2x2 C&C - 28"x28"
2x3 C&C - 28"x43"
2x4 C&C - 28"x58"
Midwest Cage - 24"x47"
***For hygienic purposes, cage liners do not come prewashed. Liners are made 2-3 inches larger in length and width to account for any shrinkage that may occur in the first washing and drying cycles. This ensures that you don't end up with a liner that is too small for your cage!
All items are handmade with love in a 100% SMOKE FREE environment. 
Fleece Use and Care:
Before first use: Machine wash and tumble dry on low or hang to dry. (*Make sure you DO NOT use fabric softener or dryer sheets) Repeat the wash and dry cycle 2 to 3 more times in order to break down the fleece's waterproof barrier and allow moisture to wick into the inner layer. Adding vinegar to the wash cycle helps this process.
To test if your fleece is ready to use: Place a drop of water onto the surface of the fleece. If the water disappears into the fabric, the liner is ready to use! If the water beads and remains on top of the fleece, repeat the wash and dry cycle then retest.
Change out your fleece liner every 4 days to 1 week of use. Before washing it's recommended to brush pet hair and debris from the liner to keep your washing machine free of gunky buildup. Wash on warm cycle with your regular detergent (make sure your detergent does not have a fabric softener additive). Vinegar can be added to the wash cycle to help neutralize any odors. Tumble dry on low or hang to dry. Remember, DO NOT USE FABRIC SOFTENERS OR DRYER SHEETS as these will replace the waterproof barrier and prevent moisture wicking.

Then building this coop and raising your own backyard chickens is the answer to your dreams!
EASY Do-It-Yourself
4' x6' CHICKEN COOP PLANS 
PDF FILE

____________________________________
EASY WEEKEND PROJECT !!!!!
The solid, raised construction, numerous wire-mesh vents  and compact size make this coop a comfortable, safe home for your chickens - winter and summer/rain or shine. 
Cleanup is easily accomplished from outside - no crawling inside the coop - using the hinged roof access. Three exterior nesting boxes also with a hinged roof make gathering eggs easy.
____________________________________________________ 
Using just basic tools - circular saw, jigsaw, hammer, electric drill/screwdriver, etc. you can easily build this coop over the course of a weekend.
 
Painted a pretty barn red, teal, or the color of your choice with a cedar shingle hinged roof and black barn hinges, the coop is attractive as well as functional. The vinyl linoleum floor inside is ready to be covered with shavings/straw and along with the hinged coop roof makes cleaning a breeze. With metal mesh air vents and three nesting boxes also with a hinged roof, the coop will make a comfortable and safe home for your chickens winter and summer.
The coop measures 4' x 6' not including the nesting boxes - large enough for 6-8 chickens to fit comfortably, or several more if all they do is sleep in it - and has three attached nesting boxes (each approximately 12" square) with a hinged lid to collect the eggs without having to go inside, two roosts, side air vents with latching doors, a latching front round vent and a latched door with a ramp for your chickens to get in and out. The coop also has a hinged roof for easy access for cleaning, refilling food and water.

Basic Ingredients: distilled water × glycerin × sorbitol × sodium cocoyl isethionate × disodium lauryl sulfosuccinate × sodium chloride × phenoxyethanol × tetrasodium edta × sweet almond oil × fragrance ×
~~What is Creme Fraiche Whipped Soap?~~
In culinary terms, creme fraiche is a thick, rich, velvety cream. Savor's whipped soap is a bubbly interpretation of this French specialty.
Fans of Savor's Creme Fraiche enjoy the fluffy texture -- I use care not to whip too much air into the cream so that just a dab goes a long way. Using a bath pouf creates the best lather, and it's so versatile it can be used as a shaving cream, bubble bath, or even a shampoo on certain hair types!
I never use parabens as a preservative, and the Creme Fraiche contains no petroleum products. 
Best used within 6 months of receipt. Oil separation and color changes may occur over time.
~~Packaging~~
The label is highly water-resistant but please take care not to scratch it roughly when wet. I package Creme Fraiche in recyclable plastic jars with lined lids to minimize leaks during shipping. Each jar is shrink-wrapped with a perforated band that you can easily peel off.

Product name: Red Ceramic Pomegranate Art / Judaica Gift for Passover / Holy Land/Jewish Home Decoration/Symbol Abundance & Fertility/Housewarming Hostess
Description:
This listing is for one pomegranate. 
They look great in a group as you can see in the photos. Or keep it in the kitchen or on a desk as a pencil or pen holder.
The juicy, red, sweet pomegranate fruit is considered a symbol of good luck,abundance, fertility and beauty. It's probably because it has a lot of seeds and sections, which symbolize the many good qualities and deeds that each one of us has done. Because of the beauty of the fruit and symbolic values​​, it is commonly sculptured and drawn for decoration. 
This handful-sized ceramic pomegranate is the perfect Judaica gift for Jewish holidays or simply a beautiful gift for a host, engagement gift or any occasion. 
Here's how I make the pomegranates:
1. beautiful pomegranates are picked from the pomegranate tree in my garden
2. I copy them into casting molds that will save the shape forever
3. From the mold, I cast a new hollow pomegranate with white clay
4. I then hand-paint it with deliciously red glaze.
5. I sign it on the bottom
Size 
Cercumference: approx. 13-1/3 inches (33-35 cm)
Height: approx. 4-1/3 inches (11-12 cm)
What my customers are saying about my pomegranates:
★★★★★ "Beautifully hand made and wrapped, they look better than real fruit!"  
★★★★★ "My ceramic pomegranate is gorgeous and looks just like the photo! Very friendly service! I'm happy!"
Crazy about pomegranates? Me too!

Product name: Custom Photo on Wood, Gift for Her, Gift for Him, Picture Frames, Personalized Gifts for Her, Girlfriend Gift, Unique Gift, Gifts for Mom
Description:
Custom photos printed directly onto beautiful, rustic basswood with bark.
• • CURRENT TURNAROUND TIME: 
2 TO 3 BUSINESS DAYS FOR ORDER COMPLETION (this could be less) AND 2 TO 3 BUSINESS DAYS FOR SHIPPING VIA USPS PRIORITY WITHIN THE US. • •
**PLEASE READ FULL DESCRIPTION**
ABOUT OUR WOOD PHOTOS:
Have your own custom photo printed directly onto round basswood, with no margins or gaps. The photograph becomes an integral part of the wood, ensuring that it will stand the test of time. The natural wood shows through the photo for a beautiful, rustic, and "worn" look. It is said that wood elements within your home can bring balance to your space and life.
♥ UPGRADES: Purchasing as a GIFT? Add-on our gift wrapping option and have your custom wood photo wrapped in a natural burlap gift bag - 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/522661329/burlap-gift-bags-gift-wrapping-add-on
 
Looking for a way to make the back of the wood as beautiful as the front? Consider adding on one of our BACK OF WOOD DESIGN upgrade options. Select from a variety of premade and personalized designs and have them ENGRAVED onto the back of your wood photo. View our back engraving upgrades here: 
https://www.etsy.com/shop/FamilyFotoFun?ref=l2-shopheader-name&section_id=17969356
 ♥
DETAILS:
• Because this is wood from a real tree, pieces may have knots which we try to place in the best spots possible for the photo provided.
• Each piece of wood will vary in wood grain, making each one completely unique.
• Measuring anywhere from 9" to 12" in width or height, depending on the direction of your photo.
• Photos will be cropped slightly around the corners/edges, as this is the only way to fit a rectangular photo onto an oval piece of wood. All important aspects of the photo should not be located along the very edges of the picture.
• Horizontal photos will be placed horizontally on the wood & vertical photos will be placed vertically unless otherwise requested.
• White ink is not printed on the wood. This allows the natural grain of the wood to show through the photo. Colors of the photo on the wood may vary slightly. 
• A clear protective coating is applied over your wood photo to help protect against stains, water and scratching.
• All wood photos come with complimentary hardware for hanging.
• The bark of the wood is not removed from the wood in order to preserve the natural look of our wood photos.
• All orders are securely packaged with extra bubble wrap for added protection during shipping. 
• Made and Handcrafted in Virginia, U.S.A
CHOOSING YOUR PHOTO:
• The better quality the photo, the better the results will be on the wood.
• A 300 dpi photo taken in good lighting will give you the best possible print results.
• Lower quality photos can be used, but please know that the quality will be the same on the wood.
• Extremely dark, blurry, grainy or low-quality photos do not typically transfer well.
• We ask that you DO NOT add any text to your photo, due to cropping reasons.
• We recommend printing your original photo from your home printer at the full page size to get an idea of how the colors (these may vary slightly) & quality will look on the wood.
HOW TO PLACE AN ORDER:
1. Purchase this wooden picture.
2. Send us a high-quality digital photo to use through:
(a) Etsy messages by clicking "Ask a Question" and simply attaching the photo(s) to the message -or-
(b) Emailing the photo(s) to WOODFOTOS [!at] GMAIL.COM

ABOUT OUR WOOD PHOTOS:
Have your own custom photo printed directly onto round basswood, with no margins or gaps. The photograph becomes an integral part of the wood, ensuring that it will stand the test of time. The natural wood shows through the photo for a beautiful, rustic, and "worn" look. It is said that wood elements within your home can bring balance to your space and life.

Looking for a way to make the back of the wood as beautiful as the front? Consider adding on one of our BACK OF WOOD DESIGN upgrade options. Select from a variety of premade and personalized designs and have them ENGRAVED onto the back of your wood photo. View our back engraving upgrades here: 
https://www.etsy.com/shop/FamilyFotoFun?ref=l2-shopheader-name&section_id=17969356
 ♥
DETAILS:
• Because this is wood from a real tree, pieces may have knots which we try to place in the best spots possible for the photo provided.
• Each piece of wood will vary in wood grain, making each one completely unique.
• Measuring anywhere from 9" to 12" in width or height, depending on the direction of your photo.
• Photos will be cropped slightly around the corners/edges, as this is the only way to fit a rectangular photo onto an oval piece of wood. All important aspects of the photo should not be located along the very edges of the picture.
• Horizontal photos will be placed horizontally on the wood & vertical photos will be placed vertically unless otherwise requested.
• White ink is not printed on the wood. This allows the natural grain of the wood to show through the photo. Colors of the photo on the wood may vary slightly. 
• A clear protective coating is applied over your wood photo to help protect against stains, water and scratching.
• All wood photos come with complimentary hardware for hanging.
• The bark of the wood is not removed from the wood in order to preserve the natural look of our wood photos.
• All orders are securely packaged with extra bubble wrap for added protection during shipping. 
• Made and Handcrafted in Virginia, U.S.A
CHOOSING YOUR PHOTO:
• The better quality the photo, the better the results will be on the wood.
• A 300 dpi photo taken in good lighting will give you the best possible print results.
• Lower quality photos can be used, but please know that the quality will be the same on the wood.
• Extremely dark, blurry, grainy or low-quality photos do not typically transfer well.
• We ask that you DO NOT add any text to your photo, due to cropping reasons.
• We recommend printing your original photo from your home printer at the full page size to get an idea of how the colors (these may vary slightly) & quality will look on the wood.

Product name: The Flower Murrini Tutorial- By Astrid Riedel
Description:
"The Flower Murrini" 
It is my pleasure to show you how to make my flower murrinis, I hope that you will feel inspired by the process and will create out of the simple steps shown in the tutorial many more flowers of your own design. 
My intention with this tutorial is to make it possible for anyone to be able to create a beautiful flower murrini, to understand the principle design elements and to apply them to other flowers.
You often hear how it can take 8 hours or more to create a Tonbodama style flower murrini, and although I admire that, I find that most of us really don’t want to spend that much time on this.
I really wanted to develop a way to make the whole process easier and faster but at the same time still create a complex looking flower. 
And so I present to you this collection of flower murrini, we will start the tutorial with the easiest flower and work to the more advanced flowers, step by step.
The tutorials are written in mind for the intermediate/advanced bead maker. Good heat control is essential to achieve the desired results. 
Easy to follow photographs will lead you through the tutorial. With each photograph, there are concise written explanations.
In addition to learning how to make great flower murrinis, I have also added a full tutorial  demonstrating how to apply the murrini to the bead, In both the making of the murrini and the application I have developed my own techniques to bring out the beauty and the mystery of the flower murrinis. 
The 5 individual tutorials comprises of: 
An introduction 
Materials and tool requirements 
Glass requirements
Part 1 the Daisy flower
Part 2 the Daffodil flower
Part 3 the Anemone flower
Part 4 the Pink daisy flower
Part 5 the Application of the flower murrinis
The tutorials are available as instant download as soon as payment is made.
Unfortunately I cannot accept any returns, due to the fact that is digital information.
If you have any question please contact me.
Please respect my work and efforts not to copy or forward it to any other person. 
These tutorials are for your personal benefit to increase your skills and not to TEACH or be used in workshops. Thank you :) 
                                                              Astrid Riedel

Description:
Merino Wool
Long Haired
Powder Puff
4-5.5" wide 
The hair is long but can be squished
Please pick the color ribbon you would like.
These are handmade and each one varies a bit.
We Have: 
Dark Blue -3
Burgundy -3
Light Blue -1
Purple - 3
Lovely, Soft, and Large!
Historically, powder puffs have been made from various fine feathers, luscious wools, or poofy cotton. I wanted to bring you a historical powder puff that was really versatile, soft, and able to handle a lot of powder for the body or hair. Merino Wool has been around for centuries. It was highly prized and would have been very much cherished. This puff would work for your historical toilette from the Middle Ages through today.
History on Merino Wool:
It was highly valued already in the Middle Ages. Today, Merinos are still regarded as having some of the finest and softest wool of any sheep. Before the 18th century, the export of Merinos from Spain was a crime punishable by death. 
In the 18th century, small exportation of Merinos from Spain and local sheep were used as the foundation of Merino flocks in other countries. In 1723, some were exported to Sweden, by 1774 to Saxony, 1775 to Hungary and to Prussia in 1786. In 1786, Louis XVI of France received 366 sheep selected from 10 different cabañas. In 1802, Colonel David Humphreys, United States Ambassador to Spain, introduced the Vermont strain into North America. The British embargo on wool and wool clothing exports to the U.S. prior to the 1812 British/U.S. war led to a "Merino Craze" and everyone wanted Merino Wool.
Care for your puff: Feel free to shake your puff out or gently comb through it to remove any excess powder.

Product name: Viking board games Tafl (Hnefatafl) and Nine Man Morris
Description:
This is a two sided board game set that has Hnefatafl (more commonly known as Tafl) on one side, and Nine Man Morris on the other.  The board is made from hand colored duck cloth fabric, so no two are the same (the photo shows a typical stain coloring).  The images on the boards are hand printed, and given a slightly distressed look.  The set comes with all the pieces to play both games, as well as instructions.
Tafl is an ancient Viking board game that was the most played game in Europe prior to the introduction of chess.  It is identified in the Viking Sagas as an important element for a warrior to learn and play well in order to become successful.  It is also one of a very few games that has an uneven player starting point.  The "Swedes" are out numbered two to one by "Muscovites" at the start of the game.  It is a very fun, and interesting game, with different strategies for each side.
Nine Man Morris is an ancient game from Rome that is often found on the back of Tafl boards.  It is a very fast paced game that has some similarities to checkers.
The board is approximately 11" by 15" and the playing pieces are approximately 3/4" each.

All ports are clear and open for easy access. The front edge is raised slightly to protect the screen when laying your phone flat on it’s face, pretty side up.
TOUGH
For more shock absorbency, upgrade to the Tough case with an added TPU liner. The liner can be seen around the edges of the plastic shell. The raised bumper adds a bit of screen protection. Cutouts in the liner and soft touch button covers allow access to all of your phone’s ports and functions. The outer shell of the tough case is a tad bigger than the slim to have room for all this goodness, and cannot be used without the liner.
White liners are now available for iPhone 6, 6S, 7, 6 Plus and 6S Plus and 7 Plus Tough cases. All other device types have only black liners.

Product name: retro telephone, telephone, antique telephone, telephone Karbolit, Black telephone, telephone vintage, Karbolit, decor, design, vintage
Description:
Phone Karbolit USSR 1960s
Phone is in perfect vintage condition!
Few people know that in the Soviet Union prior to 1968, the telephone numbers were not just numbers but also letters. And first phones dialer did not exist. In the book "the List of subscribers of the Moscow telephone network" in 1916 the first paragraph of the rules of using phones reads: "the Central station is called simply by lifting the microtelephone from the cradle. Duty station should respond by telling you your room. Then the caller loudly and clearly reports the number with which communication is required".
On the first disk devices were only numbers. In 20-e years of the last century next to the figures depicted letters. In the USSR on the phone next to the number was also 10 letters: A, B, C, G, D, E, F, I, K, L (А, Б, В, Г, Д, Е, Ж, И, К, Л). the Letter Z (З) is not used, because it is similar to the three.

This custom fishing lure is our "most popular" Etsy gift! The personalized fishing lure is pictured in antiqued brass in frames 1-3 and in bronze in frames 4-5.  These lures can also be purchased in antiqued copper or stainless steel.  
These fishing lures are 100% handmade from start to finish in our small home shop. Each lure is made by hand cutting the metal into the shape of a heart. Each is then further shaped and fine tuned to eliminate rough edges. They are all given a one of a kind distressed, antiqued and varied finish.  All are then brushed and polished. They are personalized with hand stamping. Each letter is carefully hammered into the metal - one by one. The spacing and depth of the letters can vary - since this is not done by a machine. These differences make every item completely one of a kind. It should be noted that our lures can only be hand stamped on one side, not both. Finally the lures are finished off by adding swivels, split rings and hooks. They have a slight bend to them, which allows them to spin in the water - making them not only super unique, but also effective for fishing! Product name: Zine: SELF-LOVE // poetry / prose / perzine // handmade zine / handwritten zine // journal excerpts
Description:
In March 2013 I made a zine about self-love. What is it? How do I love myself currently? How can I love myself better?
In February 2015 -- on Valentine's Day, in fact! -- I revised the zine by adding new content and new sketches. Revising the zine was, in itself, a form of self-love. It emphasised the value of my voice and my thoughts. It reminded me of the little things I like to do, the little things that calm my mind and settle my heart. It forced me to look at parts of my body and consider them worthy of attention and admiration. Here is the revised zine. Enjoy. 
7.5cm x 10.5cm [approx. 3in x 4in]
32 pages
bound with white thread

Description:
***Please note: the size of this camera strap cover is 3.25" WIDE x 38" LONG. PLEASE MEASURE YOUR CURRENT FACTORY STRAP TO ENSURE THIS WILL FIT OVER IT. The lens cap pocket will fit a cap sized up to 2.50" in diameter (if you shoot with a lens greater than 58mm in ring size (aka filter size) please convo me so we can customize your strap to fit the bigger lens cap., i.e. 67mm, 72mm. The cap used to measure the pocket space in the photos is a 58mm filter.) 
This listing is for a peachy/coral flowers on teal print camera strap and is suitable for most DSLR cameras. This strap has a peach backside and lens cap pocket that is monogrammed in teal thread and is lightly padded for extra comfort. 
*For the three letter monogram option (picture 4) please indicate in the note to seller box the initials in the order that they will appear on the monogram. You can chose the upper case letter with the swirls or lower case letter seen to the right of the upper case letter in the photo for the style of the center initial on your monogram. The "D" on this camera strap is the lower case option without all the swirls on the "D" letter as shown in picture 4. The lower case option is for those not wanting a super swirly font. So for this you would pick lower case and all letters will be the lower case style. If you pick upper case then the center initial will have the swirls and be flanked by two lower case initials. 
If you have any questions, please message me and we can work on your monogram together.    
 
***pictures of font choices are embroidery files purchased from the itch2stitch. 
****Each camera strap is handmade and the fabric pattern varies with each item when the fabric is cut.
To install: 
1) Disconnect one end of your camera's strap from the camera body
2) Take the largest safety pin you can find and attach it to your camera's strap
3) Insert it in one end of the camera strap cover and begin to thread it through the strap
4) When it is all the way through, remove the pin and reattach the camera strap to the camera body
5) Enjoy!
**Due to the custom nature on monogrammed items ALL SALES ARE FINAL, NO REFUNDS, RETURNS OR EXCHANGES. Please be sure to read the listing thoroughly and message me with any questions prior to completing your purchase.**

About Paul Rand:
Probably best known for his iconic IBM logo and identity system of 1956, graphic designer Paul Rand virtually singlehandedly was responsible for changing the way American graphic artist worked in the mid-twentieth century. Highly influenced by modern artists, especially the Surrealists, Rand was known for "defamiliarizing the ordinary" as well as for his simplified typography and breaking from graphic convention. Typical "Rand-isms" include torn paper collage, handwritten type, and the use of stripes as a graphic element.
Rand's oeuvre included designs for corporate identities and logos, books and book covers, posters, advertisements, and countless other applications of ink to flat surfaces.

*MONOGRAM GUIDELINES:
Here are a few general guidelines for monogramming to make it easier for you:
For a Married Couple (or soon to be):
The monogram will contain the bride's first initial, the surname of the couple, and the groom's first initial, in that order. For instance Jennifer and Kyle Smith will be JSK
Monogramming a Gift for a Woman:
A monogrammed gift for a woman should include her first, middle and last initial or if she is married, her first, maiden name, and married name initials. Traditionally, a woman's monogram is presented in first, last, middle initial order. So for Gabriella Marie Smith, it will be GSM
Monogramming a Gift for a Man:
For men's gifts, it is very important to consider the shape of the item to be monogrammed when choosing the order of the initials. When monogramming something for a man, many people prefer to use the initials in the first, middle and last order when all the letters are the same height. For example, Robert John West will be RJW (all letters same height).  Or when the letter in the middle is bigger, you can use the same tips for a woman - first, last and middle initials (Robert John West's will be RWJ if the middle is taller than the other two initials)

Product name: Brush Lettering Starter Kit
Description:
Want to learn brush lettering? This starter kit is the perfect introduction to the beautiful art! The 22 page booklet, written by Amanda Houston, begins with an introduction to brush lettering terms, and takes you through the basic strokes used in a brush script. You will then be guided through each letter of the alphabet, in a modern calligraphy script style, with a final section on "bringing it all together" with word examples to follow, so you are fully capable of producing beautiful words when you are finished. Within the booklet, there is lined space designated for practicing each stroke and letter, as well as free space at the end to practice your new skills. The entire booklet is made up of a smooth, silk paper, that is meant to preserve the life of your pens. It is spiral bound, and can be used time and time again for reference to the basics, and practice prompts. 
Along with the booklet, you will receive two styles of brush pens: a Tombow Dual Brush pen (for larger writing), and a Pentel Sign Brush pen (for smaller writing.) Colors will vary based on supply.

Description:
Display picture features the following selections:
Size: Medium
Nail Length/Shape: Long/Ballerina
(Display nail color)
This is just listed here as an example. Please select the appropriate size, length, shape and color option to fit your needs. 
If you do not want the color pictured on the display photograph please review the color wheel pictured and send a note WITH YOUR ORDER indicating the number matching your color preference. 
If you do not send a note with your order you will receive the color displayed on the cover picture (the first picture).
You will receive a set of 10 Custom Made To Order Sassy Press On Nails, a file, a buffer block, an alcohol wipe, a storage box and detailed instructions on how to apply your sassy nails. GLUE IS NOT INCLUDED AND MUST BE PURCHASED SEPARATELY. Check out the professional strength glue that we have listed here in our store.
To determine your size please follow these simple directions: *** please measure by centimeters *** An example of this process is also listed in the picture section of each listing.
Take a flexible measuring tape and wrap it around the widest part of your nail....please be sure not to wrap it too tightly.
Measure from where the skin meets on your nail from the left to the right (sidewalls)
Be sure to measure all ten fingers because sometimes one hand may be larger than the other. If you are in between sizes its best to go with the larger size because you can always file down the sides for a better fit.
If you don't have a measuring tape available please place a piece of Scotch tape around the widest part of your nails and use a pen to mark your side walls. Remove the tape and lay it on a flat surface to measure with a ruler.
Sizing Guide: (Thumb to Pinky)
XL- 2.0cm, 1.5cm, 1.7cm, 1.5cm, 1.2cm
L- 1.8cm, 1.4cm, 1.5cm, 1.4cm, 1.1cm
M- 1.7cm, 1.3cm, 1.4cm, 1.3cm, 1.0cm
S- 1.5cm, 1.2cm, 1.3cm, 1.2cm, 9cm
XS- 1.4cm, 1.1cm, 1.2cm, 1.1cm, 8cm
** If none of the sizes listed fit you please select the "custom send in notes" option and be sure to send me a note WITH YOUR ORDER indicating your measurements in centimeters in the following format: thumb (cm), index (cm), middle (cm), ring (cm) and pinky (cm). If you do not select from the size options listed or send a note with your order indicating your measurements please understand that this will cause a delay in the processing time of your order because I am unable to process any order without your sizes/measurements.
Don't forget to send me your nail selfies once you apply your set!!! I can't wait to see them.

Product name: Stay sexy don't get murdered my favorite murder ring stamped jewelry stacking ring signet ring
Description:
Inspired by the My Favorite Murder podcast, a portion of the proceeds from this hand-stamped ring will be donated to End the Backlog, which works to eliminate the backlog of hundreds of thousands of untested rape kits. You can read more about End the Backlog here: http://www.endthebacklog.org.
Please choose sterling silver or brass. Don't see your ring size in the drop down menu? Send me a message and I can accommodate most ring sizes.
Not sure about your ring size? Stop into any jeweler or use http://findmyringsize.com/. Just remember to round up if you plan to wear a big stack. The more rings you wear on a finger, the tighter they'll feel.
Since each piece of Silversheep Jewelry is handmade to order, variations may exist in texture and finish. Please allow up to 10 days for order fulfillment prior to shipping, although it will usually be much quicker. Message me for an estimate on current shipping lead times.
About the materials used:
Silversheep jewelry is created using sterling silver, 14K yellow and rose gold fill, and genuine gemstones. It is free of nickel, lead, and cadmium and is comfortable to wear for those with a sensitivity to base metal.
Gold fill consists of a brass base coated with a layer of 14k yellow or rose gold hundreds of times thicker than plate, and with proper care will retain its finish for many years to come. It is also hypoallergenic and safe for those with metal sensitivities. As with any gold filled jewelry, the ends where the wire was cut will expose the brass core, potentially causing it to oxidize a bit over time, but it is easily buffed back up to a bright gold color. Yellow gold fill typically has a very warm golden hue, especially when heated. Please keep this in mind when making your purchase. I use 14K gold solder to solder both yellow and rose gold filled jewelry. It is strong and does not tarnish, like “yellow silver” solder. Unfortunately, the rose gold solder currently available is extremely toxic to work with, so I use yellow gold instead, resulting in slightly more visible solder seams. If this is a problem for you, I encourage you to choose one of my other color options, as a safe work environment is more important than perfectly color-matched solder!
Taking care of your jewelry:
For bright sterling silver and gold filled pieces, buff with a soft polishing cloth (nothing abrasive!). 
For oxidized and ombre pieces, please do not polish! I seal these pieces with a microcrystalline polishing wax to help preserve the finish, but there is no permanent way to seal the patina and with regular wear, the finish will continue to evolve. Avoiding contact with water, soap, and lotions will help, as will storing your pieces in a zip lock bag. Again, it's totally normal for the oxidation to lighten over time and with wear. Just think of it as your jewelry customizing specifically to you!
With these few simple steps, your Silversheep Jewelry will stay in great shape for years to come! 
Ring sizing:
Please be very careful when entering your ring size. The most accurate way to measure your ring size is to stop into any jeweler and have them measure your finger. If you're ordering a thick stack, err on the side of too large. The jeweler can also measure your finger for a "wide band". It may read up to a full size larger than your narrow band ring size. 
Please read my shop policies thoroughly before placing your order.

Product name: Small gold hoop earring, 14k gold nose ring, Hoop gold cartilage earring, gold septum piercing jewelry 6mm 22g gold tragus hoop 8mm 10mm 20g
Description:
Beautifuly simple, this small 14k gold-filled hoop earring is carefully crafted with a dainty, thin 22g, or standard 20g 14k gold-filled wire made in an infinite endless style.  Perfect for use as a nose ring, cartilage earring, or any piercing jewelry need.  These quality hoops are available in your choice of three sizes, 6mm, 8mm, or 10mm.  We carefully make all of our piercing jewelry in our Pacific northwest studio with attention to comfort and quality.
****This listing is for a single hoop.
   Size check.<<< 
The outer edge of the 8mm is the size of Home Button on the iPhone. 10mm is slightly larger.  6mm slightly smaller.  
-Hoop sizes are based on wire gauge and interior diameters.
Interior diameter size options:
6mm - very tiny and may be OK for a tiny ear that is pierced close to the edge. Possible sites include daith, tragus and rook.
8mm - slightly larger and fits more people. Possible sites include nostril, helix, daith, tragus, and second lobe.
10mm - good for a piercing farther away from the edge of the ear. Possible sites include lobe, helix, septum.
These are only estimations.  Class X wants you to be happy with your purchase.  Every piercing is different so be sure to take notice of your own for proper fit as we can not offer returns due to hygienic reasons. 
-Wire 
22 gauge - Slim wire (delicate)
20 gauge - Standard wire
14K gold filled
Item Information:
All of our cartilage and nose hoops are a seamless style,  twist open and close, and can be worn on any piercing.
Hoop Care - 
To extend the life of your hoops, please remove before bathing, swimming and sleeping.
Store in a dry, clean ziplock bag.
Sterling silver will tarnish over time.  To clean your hoops, add mild dishsoap to a bowl of warm water and let soak for a few minutes.  Gently use a soft cloth to remove any impurities, rinse and buff dry.

M A T E R I A L S
GOLD-FILLED (hypoallergenic)
14K Gold fill is a pressure bonded layer of gold that has 100 times more gold than plated jewelry. It is durable, won't chip or flake, is tarnish resistant, and a great alternative to "karat" gold that is reasonably priced, looks gorgeous and if taken care of should last for many years.
925 STERLING SILVER
Sterling Silver by definition is .925 silver and is a great silver option for those who don't wear gold. Sterling silver will oxidize and need polishing every now and then, but with the proper care and cleaning can be brought back to a shine.

Product name: Bat Tie Clip
Description:
One of our most popular tie clips, the Bat Tie Clips have a striking bat design that is set off by a carbon fiber-look decal. These tie clips are a fun way to add some extra style – and keep your tie from flopping around, blowing in the breeze or falling into your food!
I know a lot of people have bought these Bat Tie Clips for use as gifts for guys. If you’re looking for gift ideas for young men, gifts for teen boys, grad gifts for guys, or gift ideas for your boyfriend or husband, you should consider these (or one of my other designs, if he’s not the “bat” type of guy).
I have these Bat Tie Clips laser cut from from .08” thick 5052 aluminum, and then I hand bend and polish them and send them to you packaging in a nice black satin drawstring pouch. While these tie clips are made to snugly fit a medium thickness tie and shirt, they are slightly adjustable by hand bending them more or less to fit a particular tie. 
Each “standard” Bat Tie Clip is 2.25” wide, made to fit a standard 3-3.5” wide tie. I also have a skinny tie version available at 
https://www.etsy.com/listing/124543491/bat-skinny-tie-clip.
 In fact, I offer a big range of standard size and skinny tie clips, from “cool” to "sports-themed" to “conservative.” See them all at 
http://www.etsy.com/shop/KevinCossDesigns
 .
*** PLEASE READ
Buyer is responsible for any applicable customs fees if shipping out of the US. Also, the standard price international shipping does take a long time, sometimes as long as a month. I recommend upgrading to priority mail at checkout if you need your tie clip sooner!

Description:
These are my awesome "Green fuzzy furry Feet" Slipper Socks in  Green. I hand knit these w/ 100% wool in this fabulous shade of  Green . Which sole material should you choose?

Rubber Sole: Meant for walking and standing babies. Non slip and water and heat resistant.

With a tape measure (not a ruler!) and with baby lying on the ground, please measure your baby’s foot from the very bottom of the heel to the very tip of the longest toe and then choose the size that your baby’s foot length falls under:

Product name: Tooled Leather Belt - Custom Leather Belt - Personalized Leather Belt - Brown 1-1/2" SND Pattern
Description:
This is a 1-1/2" handcrafted leather belt with a lovely scrolled pattern.  All of my belts are custom made using 8 oz. double shoulder leather and are hand tooled by me and NEVER embossed.  This custom leather belt is block-dyed a medium brown and ready to be sized up to a size 44".  Just note the size when ordering (please see IMPORTANT NOTE below before ordering).
It comes with a brass plated buckle which is held securely in place by two snaps.  The use of snaps allows you to easily swap out the buckle with a designer/western style buckle or other buckle of your choice.
I can personalize your custom leather belt with a name at no additional charge.  Just note the name when ordering.  I use 3/4" letters as seen in the slide above. 
To see other belt patterns available, click here   
www.etsy.com/shop/HawkinsLeather?section_id=13127688
IMPORTANT NOTE:  IT IS THE BUYER'S RESPONSIBILITY TO ORDER THE CORRECT BELT SIZE.  Order your custom leather belt 2" LARGER than your pant size (i.e., 36" pant size = 38" belt).  Or, better yet, measure around your waist or hips, wherever you will wear the belt, and ADD 2" to that measurement.  If you will be wearing a designer/western style buckle with this belt DO NOT add the 2", as the designer/western style buckle adds 2" to the length of the belt.  I punch 5 holes in all of my custom leather belts.  The center hole will be at the measurement you order, with two holes on either side.  Because the belts are custom made to fit you individually, if the belt does not fit, I cannot issue a refund or remake the belt.  If you are not sure or have questions, PLEASE ask before ordering, I am more than happy to assist you in ordering the correct size.
